# Frontend Environment Variables

## Required

# Backend API URL
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:3001

## Optional

# Enable performance metrics dashboard in development
NEXT_PUBLIC_ENABLE_METRICS=true

# Bundle analyzer (set to true to analyze bundle)
ANALYZE=false

# Node environment (automatically set)
# NODE_ENV=development

## Development vs Production

### Development (.env.local)
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:3001
NEXT_PUBLIC_ENABLE_METRICS=true
ANALYZE=false

### Production
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://your-backend.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_ENABLE_METRICS=false

## Notes

- All variables prefixed with `NEXT_PUBLIC_` are exposed to the browser
- `.env.local` is gitignored and used for local development
- Set production variables in your deployment platform (Vercel, etc.)
- PWA service worker is disabled in development mode automatically
